The paper deals with detecting suspicious behavior in web platforms, which involves analyzing multiple attributes of entities and their relationships. This suggests a focus on social networks and information retrieval, as well as data mining and databases. The use of graph mining and multi-view analysis further supports these categories. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computers and Society), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.DB (Databases).
